  "contentHtml": "\n        \n                <ul>\n                    \n                     <li><a href=\"/news/hospitals\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Hospitals</a></li>                     <li>2 min read</li>                 </ul>\n                            \n        \n                                    \n\n                                                                            <p><img src=\"https://health.economictimes.indiatimes.com/Themes/Release/theme4/images/icons/et-default-user.svg\" alt=\"Online Bureau\">\n                                            \n                                        </p>\n                                                                        \n                                                                                    <ul>\n                                                                                                    <li>\n                                                                                                                    <a>Online Bureau</a>\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                                                                                                            </li>\n                                                                                                                                                    <li><a href=\"/agency/88675629/ETHealthWorld\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ETHealthWorld</a></li>\n                                                                                            </ul>\n                                                                                <ul>\n                                                                                            <li>Updated On Mar 10, 2026 at 04:28 PM IST</li>\n                                                                                                                                </ul>\n                                    \n                                                                            \n                                                                        \n                                \n                                \n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure> Mumbai: Philips has partnered with <a href=\"/tag/advanced+centre+for+treatment\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Advanced Centre for Treatment</a>, Research and Education in Cancer (ACTREC), a unit of <a href=\"/tag/tata+memorial+centre\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Tata Memorial Centre</a>, to introduce next-generation <a href=\"/tag/spectral+ct+imaging\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Spectral CT imaging</a> aimed at improving <a href=\"/tag/early+cancer+detection\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">early cancer detection</a> and <a href=\"/tag/diagnostic+precision\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">diagnostic precision</a> in India.The collaboration brings the Philips Spectral CT 7500 platform to ACTREC, enabling clinicians to capture detailed spectral information during routine CT scans. The technology allows deeper disease characterisation from a single scan, helping clinicians make faster and more confident diagnostic decisions without increasing radiation exposure.<!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        According to the company, the system provides detailed imaging insights in a single scan and enables full-body examinations in around two seconds. Studies indicate the technology can reduce the need for additional diagnostic procedures by about 36 per cent in complex cancer evaluations, potentially lowering patient anxiety, radiation exposure and treatment delays.<!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->The move comes as India faces a rising burden of cancer and other complex diseases, where timely and accurate diagnosis remains critical, particularly in high-volume tertiary care centres.“By embedding Spectral CT into routine clinical practice, we aim to help healthcare teams reduce diagnostic delays, minimise unnecessary scans and improve access to timely diagnosis,” said Bharath Sesha, managing director, Philips Indian Subcontinent.<!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->Pankaj Chaturvedi, director, ACTREC, <a href=\"/tag/tata+memorial+centre\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Tata Memorial Centre</a>, said the installation of the advanced imaging platform reflects the institute’s focus on integrating cutting-edge technologies into clinical practice to enhance patient care and support faster treatment decisions.The Spectral CT platform is expected to support multiple clinical specialties including oncology, cardiology, neurology and emergency medicine, where rapid and accurate assessment is essential for improving outcomes.<!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->During a joint clinical programme on Spectral CT held at ACTREC on February 7, a publication titled Spectral CT: Clinical Publication Compendium was unveiled. The compendium brings together more than 770 peer-reviewed publications and white papers highlighting the clinical applications of <a href=\"/tag/spectral+ct+imaging\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">spectral CT imaging</a> across various medical disciplines.\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        Philips said the initiative is part of its broader efforts to strengthen India’s diagnostic infrastructure, while ACTREC continues to adopt advanced technologies to enhance cancer care and support the evolution of oncology practice in the country.                    \n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                                                            <!-- <li>By <span>Online Bureau</span>,</li> -->\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <li>By\n                                                                                            <a>Online Bureau</a>\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                        , \n                                                                                    </li>\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/88675629/ETHealthWorld\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ETHealthWorld</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On Mar 10, 2026 at 04:28 PM IST</li> -->\n                                    <li>Published On Mar 3, 2026 at 03:30 PM IST</li>\n                                    <!-- <li class=\"desktop-view\">2 min read</li> -->\n                                </ul>\n                            \n                                        \n\n                    \n\n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n\n                    \n                      \n    \n            <p>\n                </p><h2>Join 